content:
Assign in Bulk with Mass Shift Update

Workforce Engagement is available in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions. Shift Scheduling is available in the Contact Center SKU, Einstein 1 Service Edition, and Service Suites.

To assign shifts to agents and update shift statuses in bulk:

*   Shift Scheduling Planner
*   Workforce Engagement Planner

Open Shifts in the App Launcher. In either the schedule or table view, click Mass Shift Update. Select an action: update shift status, assign shifts, or both. Define criteria that selects which shifts to modify.

Specify a date range, service territories, and job profiles. If you want to change shift status, specify which status to change and the status to update it to. Select shifts within a 90-day timespan. We recommend selecting less than 50,000 shifts at once.

Click the button to start the update process. A Shift Scheduling Operation record tracks progress. To learn if the update process is completed, open the Shift Scheduling Operation record. The record shows information about the process and its status, together with how many shifts were considered, how many were successfully processed, and how many failed.
title: Mass Shift Update in Service Cloud
